ay%20not%20be%20too%20concerned%20about%20whether%20the%20machines%20threaten%20their%20jobs.%20For%20example%2C%20PwC's%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pwc.com%2Fgx%2Fen%2Fissues%2Fworkforce%2Fhopes-and-fears-2022.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobal%20workforce%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20only%20a%20third%20of%20participants%20said%20they%20were%20concerned%20about%20their%20jobs%20being%20replaced%20by%20technology%20by%202025.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20findings%20indicate%20that%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20workers%3Cem%3E%20are%3C%2Fem%3E%20fearful%20about%20AI's%20potential%20threat.%20That%20fear%20probably%20hasn't%20been%20helped%20by%20predictions%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fpress%2F2020%2F10%2Frecession-and-automation-changes-our-future-of-work-but-there-are-jobs-coming-report-says-52c5162fce%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20one%20from%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20found%20that%20AI%20is%20expected%20to%20replace%20about%2085%20million%20jobs%20by%202025.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReports%20that%20robots%20are%20being%20deployed%20in%20warehouses%20to%20help%20with%20labor%20shortages%20may%20have%20also%20prompted%20anxiety.%20Amazon%20announced%20in%20October%20that%20it's%20testing%20humanoid%20robots%20called%20Digit%20in%20its%20warehouses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgility%20Robotics%2C%20the%20company%20Amazon%20is%20partnering%20with%20for%20the%20pilot%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20machines%20are%20designed%20to%20help%20humans%2C%20not%20supersede%20us.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDigit%20can%20handle%20bulk%20material%20handling%20within%20warehouses%20and%20distribution%20centers%2C%20and%20potentially%20help%20ease%20the%20labor%20shortage.%20There%20are%20projected%20to%20be%20about%20one%20million%20openings%20for%20hand%20laborers%20and%20material%20movers%20over%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fooh%2Ftransportation-and-material-moving%2Fhand-laborers-and-material-movers.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20showed%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20aren't%20enough%20workers%20for%20these%20jobs%2C%20so%20what's%20far%20more%20dire%20than%20any%20perceived%20fears%20about%20job%20replacement%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20health%20of%20these%20businesses%20is%20at%20stake%2C%26quot%3B%20Damion%20Shelton%2C%20CEO%20of%20Agility%20Robotics%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDeploying%20robots%20in%20warehouses%20to%20plug%20the%20labor%20gaps%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20they%20will%20replace%20humans.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20long%20history%20of%20technological%20anxiety%20about%20automation%20and%20jobs%2C%20but%20it's%20definitely%20not%20robots%20or%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20Shelton%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20robot%20is%20meant%20to%20complement%20people%20and%20let%20workers%20be%20more%20productive%20by%20taking%20on%20dangerous%2C%20repetitive%20tasks%20so%20people%20can%20focus%20on%20the%20more%20interesting%2C%20creative%20aspects.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ETexas-based%20Apptronik%20launched%20its%20humanoid%20robot%2C%20Apollo%2C%20in%20August.%20It%20signed%20a%20deal%20to%20partner%20with%20NASA%20last%20year%20and%20hopes%20to%20use%20them%20in%20space%20exploration.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECEO%20Jeff%20Cardenas%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20step%20for%20Apollo%20is%20to%20help%20out%20there%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20big%20labor%20shortage.%20In%20his%20view%2C%20robots%20can%20do%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20what%20humans%20can%2C%20but%20often%20the%20unfavorable%20tasks.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BYou'll%20hear%20people%20used%20the%20term%20'the%203%20Ds'%3A%20the%20dull%2C%20the%20dirty%2C%20and%20the%20dangerous%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20pair%20people%20with%20machines%20%E2%80%94%20man%20and%20machine%20%E2%80%94%20as%20opposed%20to%20man%20versus%20machine%2C%20then%20you%20can%20really%20amplify%20what%20people%20are%20capable%20of%20doing.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20Apptronik%20cofounder%20said%20robots%20can%20free%20up%20human%20workers%20from%20dangerous%20tasks%20and%20allow%20people%20to%20spend%20their%20time%20in%20better%20ways.%20He%20likened%20the%20era%20of%20work-based%20humanoid%20robotics%20to%20computing%20advances%20in%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20is%20like%20the%20early%20'80s%20of%20the%20personal%20computer%20where%20the%20early%20adopters%20are%20basically%20making%20their%20bets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20companies%20that%20we%20are%20working%20with%20have%20entire%20teams%20that%20are%20dedicated%20to%20general%20purpose%20robots%20because%20it%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20really%20transform%20the%20way%20that%20they%20do%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20humanoid%20robots%20are%20relatively%20limited%20in%20functionality%2C%20but%20he%20predicts%20the%20technology%20will%20advance%20quickly%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThe%20robots%20will%20do%20the%20things%20that%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20do%2C%20that%20injure%20us%2C%20that%20drive%20people%20out%20of%20these%20industries%2C%20and%20it'll%20allow%20people%20to%20gain%20new%20skills%20and%20do%20work%20in%20new%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20Cardenas%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt'll%20start%20in%20the%20supply%20chain%20and%20start%20in%20these%20activities%20where%20we%20have%20the%20technology%20today.%20The%20sky's%20the%20limit%20for%20where%20it%20goes%20from%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhumanoid-robots-jobs-manufacturing-tech-workforce-data-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A170