-roadways-florida-declines-320m-federal-funds-2023-12%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFlorida%2520officials%2520turned%2520down%2520%2524320%2Cin%2520the%2520next%2520fiscal%2520year%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELow-lying%20coastal%20cities%20are%20especially%20at%20risk%20of%20flood%20damage%20brought%20on%20by%20rising%20seawaters%2C%20leaving%20much%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fto-avoid-politicization-roadways-florida-declines-320m-federal-funds-2023-12%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFlorida%2520officials%2520turned%2520down%2520%2524320%2Cin%2520the%2520next%2520fiscal%2520year%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlorida%20in%20a%20path%20of%20potential%20destruction%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20model%20flood%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPhysics-based%20flood%20models%20that%20rely%20on%20standard%20computing%20power%20were%20once%20the%20norm%20in%20flood%20prediction%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness-67748255%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20models%20are%20prone%20to%20underestimating%20the%20real%20risk%20of%20incoming%20flooding%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.northeastern.edu%2F2023%2F12%2F04%2Fflood-prediction-artificial-intelligence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENortheastern%20Global%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20citing%20an%20incident%20in%20Waverly%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20in%20August%202021%20when%2020%20people%20died%20after%20meteorologists%20predicted%20two%20to%20three%20inches%20of%20rain%20but%20wound%20up%20with%20more%20than%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20at%20least%2077%20US%20flood%20fatalities%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weather.gov%2Farx%2Fusflood%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Weather%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtificial%20intelligence%20models%2C%20however%2C%20study%20not%20just%20the%20weather%20forecast%20but%20the%20nearby%20land%20and%20rivers%2C%20drainage%20information%20about%20the%20area%2C%20and%20regional%20layout%20to%20create%20more%20comprehensive%20predictive%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Residents%20cross%20a%20road%20damaged%20during%20flooding%20in%20Tana%20River%20county%20in%20Kenya.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656cb2f27a3c8094d5d90679%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResidents%20cross%20a%20road%20damaged%20during%20flooding.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Inganga%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20BBC%2C%20AI%20also%20has%20superior%20computing%20power%2C%20meaning%20models%20can%20do%20the%20work%20much%20quicker%20and%20with%20less%20human%20oversight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20firm%20employing%20AI%20is%207Analytics%2C%20a%20Norway-based%20sustainability%20data%20platform%20focusing%20on%20climate%20risk%20management.%20The%20company%20already%20uses%20its%20AI%20model%20to%20provide%20real-time%20flooding%20predictions%20for%20local%20businesses%20and%20authorities%2C%20pinpointing%20at-risk%20areas%2C%20according%20to%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20founder%20Jonas%20Borland%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20the%20model%20can%20predict%20up%20to%20seven%20days%20before%20a%20catastrophic%20weather%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20this%20data%20takes%20into%20account%20where%20the%20water%20will%20flow%2C%20and%20where%20it%20will%20create%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20tell%20you%20that%20in%20five%20days%20you%20will%20have%2050%20cm%20of%20water%20at%20your%20entrance%2C%20and%20we%20can%20tell%20you%20when%20it%20will%20subside.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETorland%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20donations%20and%20funding%20for%20the%20model%20have%20increased%20recently%20as%20awareness%20of%20flood%20risks%20has%20become%20more%20commonplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBig%20names%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENeara%2C%20a%20London-based%20infrastructure%20modeling%20platform%2C%20uses%20AI%20to%20make%20digital%20simulations%20of%20floods%20that%20help%20electricity%20networks%20prepare%20for%20and%20respond%20to%20water%20damage%2C%20The%20BBC%20reported.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Iowa%20also%20has%20an%20AI%20model%20called%20Flood%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20Google%20has%20gotten%20in%20on%20the%20AI%20game%2C%20providing%20river%20flood%20warnings%20across%20more%20than%2080%20countries%20with%20its%20Flood%20Hub%20platform%2C%20which%20launched%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFloods%20are%20one%20of%20the%20most%20devastating%20natural%20disasters%2C%20and%20impact%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20people%20per%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Yossi%20Matias%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20engineering%20and%20research%20and%20crisis%20response%20lead%20at%20Google%2C%20told%20the%20BBC%20%26quot%3BWe%20really%20want%20to%20let%20people%20know%20before%20floods%20actually%20hit%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20system%20uses%20satellite%20images%20to%20make%20pictures%20of%20rivers%20and%20nearby%20terrain%2C%20which%20AI%20then%20uses%20to%20predict%20how%20rivers%20could%20flood%20following%20rainfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlood%20Hub%20researchers%20told%20the%20BBC%20that%20the%20system%20could%20send%20a%20warning%20anywhere%20from%20two%20to%20seven%20days%20before%20devastating%20weather%20hits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%20alone%2C%20Google%20sent%20115%20million%20flood%20alert%20messages%20to%2023%20million%20people%2C%20the%20company%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsponsored.bloomberg.com%2Farticle%2Fgoogle-sustainability%2FHow-AI-Is-Helping-Communities-Anticipate-Floods%3Fsref%3DyaJhKSOh%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esponsored%20Bloomberg%20article.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20BBC%2C%20AI%20models%20are%20especially%20helpful%20in%20places%20with%20limited%20historical%20weather%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20nature%20of%20these%20global%20models%20is%20they%20can%20actually%20learn%20from%20experiences%20happening%20in%20other%20rivers%20where%20you%20have%20more%20data%20and%20more%20historical%20experience%2C%20Matias%20told%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20AI%20models%20aren't%20a%20perfect%20solution%2C%20Amy%20McGovern%2C%20a%20computer%20scientist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oklahoma%20School%20of%20Meteorology%2C%20told%20the%20outlet.%20They%20are%20only%20as%20good%20as%20the%20data%20they%20collect%3B%20places%20that%20don't%20have%20a%20history%20of%20severe%20flooding%2C%20remain%20at%20risk%20as%20artificial%20intelligence%20races%20to%20gather%20enough%20information%20to%20predict%20the%20outcome%20of%20rare%20heavy%20rains%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-flood-prediction-save-lives-climate-change-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703639071000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658b582d1c5c7b8c9a0c2308%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-flood-prediction-save-lives-climate-change-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cities%20around%20the%20world%20could%20see%20more%20than%206%20feet%20of%20flooding%20by%202100%2C%20with%20several%20at%20risk%20of%20disappearing.%20AI%20flood%20prediction%20could%20save%20millions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-flood-prediction-save-lives-climate-change-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kanye%20apologizes%20for%20anti-Semitic%20comments%22